Class RDKitTypeConverter

    public abstract class RDKitTypeConverter
extends DataCellTypeConverter
implements RDKitTypeConversionErrorProvider
    Converter for RDKit that converts Smiles or SDF cells into an adapter cell that contains RDKit cells.
    Author:
    Thorsten Meinl, University of Konstanz, Manuel Schwarze, Novartis

      • createRDKitAdapterCellFromSdf

        public static DataCell createRDKitAdapterCellFromSdf(java.lang.String strSdf)
                                              throws RDKitTypeConverterException
        Creates an RDKit Adapter Cell from the passed in SDF string. Based on the existing SDF value we create an ROMol object and a SMILES value and from these two objects an RDKit Cell, which is put into an RDKit Adapter Cell.
        Parameters:
        strSdf - SDF string. Can be null.
        Returns:
        RDKit Adapter Cell.
        Throws:
        RDKitTypeConverterException - Thrown, if SDF could not be converted successfully.

      • determineValueClassesToSupport

        protected static java.lang.Class<? extends DataValue>[] determineValueClassesToSupport(DataType type)
        Traverses the list of RDKit supported value classes and returns only the classes that are not compatible and not adaptable with the passed in data type. Using this method we can determine, which value classes should be provided by our RDKit Adapter Cell. Example: If an cell that supports SDF value gets converted into an RDKit Adapter Cell we want to provide all possible data values that were not already provided by the original SDF cell. Exception: The RDKitMolValue will always be added as first value in the list as an RDKit Adapter Cell ALWAYS provides that data value.
        Parameters:
        type - Data type to check for already compatible / adaptable data values. Can be null, in which case we would return the array that contains only RDKitMolValue.class.
        valueClasses - Value classes to check.
        Returns:
        Array with value classes that are not compatible and not adaptable to the passed in type. As first argument RDKitMolValue.class is always added.

      • determineValueClassesToSupport

        protected static java.lang.Class<? extends DataValue>[] determineValueClassesToSupport(DataType type,
                                                                                       java.lang.Class<? extends DataValue>... valueClasses)
        Traverses the passed in list of value classes and returns only the classes that are not compatible and not adaptable with the passed in data type. Using this method we can determine, which value classes should be provided by our RDKit Adapter Cell. Example: If an cell that supports SDF value gets converted into an RDKit Adapter Cell we want to provide all possible data values that were not already provided by the original SDF cell. Exception: The RDKitMolValue will always be added as first value in the list as an RDKit Adapter Cell ALWAYS provides that data value.
        Parameters:
        type - Data type to check for already compatible / adaptable data values. Can be null, in which case we would return the array that contains only RDKitMolValue.class.
        valueClasses - Value classes to check.
        Returns:
        Array with value classes that are not compatible and not adaptable to the passed in type. As first argument RDKitMolValue.class is always added.
